## Code Hygiene

{{CODE_HYGIENE}}

## Key Conventions

{{#IF_FRONTEND}}
- **Import alias**: Use `@/*` or configured path alias for imports. Avoid deep relative paths.
- **Component organization** — organize by what the component IS:
  - `ui/` — UI library primitives (READ-ONLY if using shadcn/ui)
  - `sidebar/` — shell navigation (sidebar, header)
  - `cards/` — reusable card components
  - `banners/` — hero/banner sections
  - `widgets/` — floating/interactive widgets
  - `sections/` — page sections that compose cards/banners
  - `pages/` — full page-level content views
  - `modal/` — modal dialogs
  - Think about what the component IS, not what page it appears on.
{{/IF_FRONTEND}}
{{#IF_SHADCN}}
- **`src/components/ui/` is READ-ONLY** — never modify UI library primitives directly. Create wrappers in feature directories that import and extend them.
{{/IF_SHADCN}}
{{#IF_MUI}}
- **Material UI theming** — customize via `createTheme()`. Use `sx` prop for one-off styles. Use `styled()` for reusable styled components. Never override internal MUI class names directly.
{{/IF_MUI}}
{{#IF_ANTD}}
- **Ant Design theming** — use `ConfigProvider` with custom theme tokens. Use `Form.Item` for form fields. Never override `.ant-*` classes directly.
{{/IF_ANTD}}
{{#IF_CHAKRA}}
- **Chakra UI theming** — extend the theme via `extendTheme()`. Use component props for styling. Use responsive array syntax for breakpoints.
{{/IF_CHAKRA}}
{{#IF_ZOD}}
- **Form validation**: All Zod schemas go in a dedicated validation directory. Never define validation inline in components.
{{/IF_ZOD}}
{{#IF_YUP}}
- **Form validation**: All Yup schemas go in a dedicated validation directory. Compose schemas using `.shape()` and `.concat()`. Never define inline.
{{/IF_YUP}}
{{#IF_FORMIK}}
- **Forms**: Use Formik's `<Field>` and `<ErrorMessage>` components. Define initial values and validation schema outside the component. Use `onSubmit` handler, never manual form events.
{{/IF_FORMIK}}
{{#IF_REACT_HOOK_FORM}}
- **Forms**: Use `useForm()` with `resolver` for Zod/Yup validation. Use `Controller` for controlled inputs. Access form state via `formState`, not manual state.
{{/IF_REACT_HOOK_FORM}}
{{#IF_NICE_MODAL}}
- **Modals**: Use `@ebay/nice-modal-react` with centralized `ModalConstant` for IDs. Each modal uses `NiceModal.create()` + UI Dialog. Register in barrel file.
{{/IF_NICE_MODAL}}
{{#IF_NEXTJS}}
- **Routing**: Each major section should be a page route. Layouts provide persistent shells. Use `usePathname()` + `<Link>` for navigation.
{{/IF_NEXTJS}}
{{#IF_VUE}}
- **Vue composition**: Use `<script setup>` with Composition API. Organize logic into composables (`use*.ts`). Use `defineProps`/`defineEmits` for component contracts.
{{/IF_VUE}}
{{#IF_ANGULAR}}
- **Angular structure**: One module per feature. Use services for business logic. Prefer standalone components. Use RxJS operators properly — always unsubscribe or use `async` pipe.
{{/IF_ANGULAR}}
{{#IF_SVELTE}}
- **Svelte structure**: Use `$:` for reactive declarations. Use stores for shared state. Keep components small — extract logic into separate `.ts` files.
{{/IF_SVELTE}}
{{#IF_ASTRO}}
- **Astro architecture**: Use islands for interactive components. Content collections for structured data. Prefer static rendering unless SSR is needed for that page.
{{/IF_ASTRO}}

{{#IF_RTK_QUERY}}
## Service Layer (RTK Query)

- **`src/services/api/`** — RTK Query services ONLY. Each file extends the base API factory. One service per domain.
- **Base service** — Network setup only (JWT injection, error handling). Do NOT add business logic.
- **Service registry** — When adding a new service, register in 3 places: reducers, middleware, and re-export.
- **Tag constants** — All RTK cache tags in a centralized constant file. Never define tags inline. Use `Object.values()` for tag arrays.
- **Request/Response types** — All DTOs in dedicated model directories. Never define types inline in service files.
{{/IF_RTK_QUERY}}

{{#IF_REDUX}}
## State Management (Redux)

- **Slices**: One slice per domain in `store/` or `slices/`. Use `createSlice` for reducers and actions.
- **Selectors**: Define reusable selectors with `createSelector`. Colocate selectors with their slice.
- **Async**: Use `createAsyncThunk` for async operations. Handle loading/error/success states in `extraReducers`.
- **Normalize state**: Use flat, normalized state shape. Avoid nesting entities.
{{/IF_REDUX}}

{{#IF_ZUSTAND}}
## State Management (Zustand)

- **One store per domain** — avoid a single monolithic store. Split by feature/concern.
- **Selectors**: Always use selectors to access state — `useStore(state => state.count)`, not `useStore()`.
- **Middleware**: Use `persist` for local storage, `devtools` for debugging. Configure in store creation.
- **Actions**: Define actions inside the store. Keep them focused and named descriptively.
{{/IF_ZUSTAND}}

{{#IF_JOTAI}}
## State Management (Jotai)

- **Atoms**: One atom per piece of state. Name descriptively (`userAtom`, `themeAtom`).
- **Derived atoms**: Use `atom((get) => ...)` for computed state. Avoid redundant state.
- **Atom families**: Use `atomFamily` for parameterized state (e.g., per-item state).
{{/IF_JOTAI}}

{{#IF_MOBX}}
## State Management (MobX)

- **Stores**: One observable store class per domain. Use `makeAutoObservable` in constructor.
- **Actions**: All state mutations must be in actions. Use `runInAction` for async mutations.
- **Computed**: Use `get` for derived values. MobX auto-tracks dependencies.
- **Reactions**: Use `reaction` or `autorun` sparingly — prefer computed values.
{{/IF_MOBX}}

{{#IF_TANSTACK_QUERY}}
## Data Fetching (TanStack Query)

- **Query keys**: Use query key factories — `queryKeys.users.list()`, `queryKeys.users.detail(id)`. Never use inline string keys.
- **Custom hooks**: One custom hook per query/mutation — `useUsers()`, `useCreateUser()`. Colocate with the feature.
- **Cache invalidation**: Use `queryClient.invalidateQueries()` after mutations. Match keys precisely.
- **Optimistic updates**: Use `onMutate` for instant UI feedback. Rollback in `onError`.
{{/IF_TANSTACK_QUERY}}

{{#IF_SWR}}
## Data Fetching (SWR)

- **Key conventions**: Use descriptive keys — `/api/users`, `/api/users/${id}`. Define a shared fetcher.
- **Revalidation**: Configure `revalidateOnFocus`, `revalidateOnReconnect` per use case. Use `mutate()` for manual revalidation.
- **Global config**: Set default options in `SWRConfig` provider.
{{/IF_SWR}}

{{#IF_APOLLO}}
## Data Fetching (Apollo Client)

- **Queries/Mutations**: Colocate GraphQL operations with the components that use them. Use `useQuery`/`useMutation` hooks.
- **Cache**: Use normalized cache. Define `typePolicies` for custom cache behavior.
- **Fragments**: Use fragments for reusable field selections. Colocate with components.
- **Error handling**: Configure `errorPolicy` per query. Use `onError` link for global error handling.
{{/IF_APOLLO}}

{{#IF_TRPC}}
## API Layer (tRPC)

- **Routers**: One router per domain. Compose into `appRouter` via `mergeRouters` or `router()`.
- **Procedures**: Name descriptively — `users.list`, `users.create`. Use `input` validation with Zod.
- **Type inference**: Let tRPC infer types — never manually type API responses.
- **Middleware**: Use for auth, logging, rate limiting. Chain via `.use()`.
{{/IF_TRPC}}

{{#IF_NESTJS}}
## Backend Conventions (NestJS)

- **Module structure**: One module per domain. Each module has controller, service, and DTOs.
- **DTOs**: All in dedicated DTO files with class-validator decorators. Never accept raw objects.
- **Guards**: Use guards for auth. Mark public endpoints explicitly.
- **Pipes**: Use ValidationPipe globally. DTOs handle validation.
- **Interceptors**: Use for response transformation and logging.
{{/IF_NESTJS}}

{{#IF_PYTHON}}
## Python Conventions

- **Type hints**: Use type hints on all function signatures. Use `from __future__ import annotations` for modern syntax.
- **Imports**: Group imports in order: stdlib, third-party, local. Use absolute imports.
- **Virtual environments**: Always use `venv` or `poetry` for dependency isolation.
{{/IF_PYTHON}}

{{#IF_DJANGO}}
## Django Conventions

- **Models**: One model per concept. Use `Meta` class for ordering, constraints. Always add `__str__`.
- **Migrations**: Run `makemigrations` after model changes. Never edit migrations manually.
- **Views**: Prefer class-based views (CBV) for CRUD, function-based views (FBV) for custom logic.
- **URLs**: Use `path()` with named routes. Namespace per app.
- **Settings**: Use environment variables for secrets. Split settings into base/dev/prod.
- **Serializers**: All DRF serializers in dedicated `serializers.py`. Never define inline.
{{/IF_DJANGO}}

{{#IF_FASTAPI}}
## FastAPI Conventions

- **Routers**: One router per domain in `routers/` directory. Register in `app.include_router()`.
- **Pydantic models**: All request/response schemas in `schemas/`. Never define inline.
- **Dependency injection**: Use `Depends()` for shared logic (auth, db sessions).
- **Async**: Use `async def` for I/O-bound endpoints. Use sync for CPU-bound.
- **Error handling**: Raise `HTTPException` with specific status codes.
{{/IF_FASTAPI}}

{{#IF_FLASK}}
## Flask Conventions

- **Blueprints**: One blueprint per feature domain. Register in app factory.
- **App factory**: Use `create_app()` pattern for configuration.
- **Routes**: Group related routes in blueprints. Use `url_for()` for URL generation.
{{/IF_FLASK}}

{{#IF_PHP}}
## PHP Conventions

- **PSR-4 autoloading**: Follow namespace-to-directory mapping. One class per file.
- **PSR-12 coding style**: Follow standard coding style. Use automated formatters.
- **Type declarations**: Use strict types (`declare(strict_types=1)`) in all files.
- **Never use raw superglobals**: Use framework Request objects instead of `$_GET`, `$_POST`, `$_REQUEST`.
{{/IF_PHP}}

{{#IF_LARAVEL}}
## Laravel Conventions

- **Eloquent models**: One model per table. Define `$fillable` or `$guarded`. Use relationships and scopes.
- **Migrations**: Use artisan to generate. Never edit existing migrations in production.
- **Controllers**: One resource controller per model. Use Form Requests for validation.
- **Form Requests**: All validation in dedicated Form Request classes. Never validate in controllers.
- **Resources**: Use API Resources for response transformation. Never return raw models.
- **Service pattern**: Extract business logic into services. Controllers handle HTTP only.
{{/IF_LARAVEL}}

{{#IF_SYMFONY}}
## Symfony Conventions

- **Controllers**: Extend `AbstractController`. One controller per feature area.
- **Services**: Use autowiring. Inject dependencies via constructor.
- **Doctrine entities**: One entity per table. Use repositories for queries.
- **Forms**: Use Form types for validation and data transformation.
{{/IF_SYMFONY}}

{{#IF_GO}}
## Go Conventions

- **Package organization**: One package per directory. Name packages as short nouns. Avoid `util`, `common`, `misc`.
- **Error handling**: Always check errors — `if err != nil { return err }`. Wrap errors with context using `fmt.Errorf("operation: %w", err)`.
- **Interfaces**: Define interfaces where they're used, not where they're implemented. Keep interfaces small.
- **Naming**: Exported names are `PascalCase`. Unexported are `camelCase`. Acronyms are all-caps (`HTTPClient`, not `HttpClient`).
- **Formatting**: `gofmt` is non-negotiable. Run `goimports` for import organization.
- **Testing**: Tests in `_test.go` files. Use table-driven tests. Use `testify` for assertions if available.
{{/IF_GO}}

{{#IF_GIN}}
## Gin Conventions

- **Router groups**: Group routes by resource — `v1 := r.Group("/api/v1")`.
- **Middleware**: Use `r.Use()` for global middleware. Group-level middleware for scoped concerns.
- **Binding**: Use `ShouldBindJSON()` for request binding with validation. Return specific error messages.
- **Error responses**: Use consistent JSON error format — `c.JSON(code, gin.H{"error": message})`.
{{/IF_GIN}}

{{#IF_RUST}}
## Rust Conventions

- **Error handling**: Use `Result<T, E>` and the `?` operator. Avoid `.unwrap()` except in tests. Define custom error types with `thiserror`.
- **Module structure**: One module per file. Use `mod.rs` or file-as-module. Re-export public API from `lib.rs`.
- **Ownership**: Prefer borrowing (`&T`) over cloning. Use `Arc<T>` for shared ownership in async code.
- **Formatting**: `cargo fmt` is mandatory. `cargo clippy` must pass with no warnings.
- **Traits**: Use traits for abstraction. Implement standard traits (`Display`, `Debug`, `From`) where appropriate.
- **Async**: Use `tokio` runtime. Use `async fn` with `.await`. Avoid blocking in async code.
{{/IF_RUST}}

{{#IF_AXUM}}
## Axum Conventions

- **Router**: Compose routes with `Router::new().route()`. Use `nest()` for sub-routers.
- **Extractors**: Use extractors for request parsing — `Json<T>`, `Path<T>`, `Query<T>`, `State<T>`.
- **Middleware**: Use tower middleware. Apply with `.layer()`. Order matters (last added = first executed).
- **Error handling**: Return `impl IntoResponse`. Define custom error types that implement `IntoResponse`.
{{/IF_AXUM}}

{{#IF_RUBY}}
## Ruby Conventions

- **Naming**: `snake_case` for methods and variables. `PascalCase` for classes/modules. `SCREAMING_SNAKE` for constants.
- **Methods**: Use `?` suffix for boolean methods. Use `!` suffix for dangerous/mutating methods.
- **Blocks**: Use `{}` for single-line blocks. Use `do...end` for multi-line blocks.
- **Gems**: Keep Gemfile organized by group (production, development, test).
{{/IF_RUBY}}

{{#IF_RAILS}}
## Rails Conventions

- **MVC**: Follow Rails conventions strictly — models in `app/models/`, controllers in `app/controllers/`, views in `app/views/`.
- **ActiveRecord**: Use scopes for reusable queries. Use validations on models. Use callbacks sparingly.
- **Routes**: RESTful routes via `resources`. Use `namespace` and `scope` for organization. Named routes everywhere.
- **Strong parameters**: Always use `params.require(:model).permit(:field1, :field2)`. Never trust user input.
- **Service objects**: Extract complex business logic into `app/services/`. Keep controllers thin.
- **Background jobs**: Use Sidekiq/ActiveJob. Keep jobs idempotent and small.
{{/IF_RAILS}}

{{#IF_JAVA}}
## Java Conventions

- **Package structure**: Organize by layer (`controller`, `service`, `repository`, `model`, `dto`, `config`).
- **Naming**: Classes are `PascalCase`. Methods/variables are `camelCase`. Constants are `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`.
- **Immutability**: Prefer immutable objects. Use `final` fields. Use builder pattern for complex objects.
- **Optional**: Use `Optional<T>` for return types that may be absent. Never use `Optional` as a parameter.
- **Streams**: Use Java streams for collection operations. Keep stream chains readable.
{{/IF_JAVA}}

{{#IF_SPRING_BOOT}}
## Spring Boot Conventions

- **Layered architecture**: Controller → Service → Repository. Never skip layers.
- **Annotations**: `@RestController` for APIs. `@Service` for business logic. `@Repository` for data access.
- **DTOs**: Map between entities and DTOs. Never expose entities directly in API responses.
- **Exception handling**: Use `@ControllerAdvice` with `@ExceptionHandler` for global error handling.
- **Profiles**: Use `application-{profile}.yml` for environment-specific config. Secrets via environment variables.
- **Dependency injection**: Use constructor injection. Avoid `@Autowired` on fields.
{{/IF_SPRING_BOOT}}

{{#IF_DOTNET}}
## .NET Conventions

- **Namespace**: Match namespace to folder structure. One type per file.
- **Async/Await**: Use `async Task<T>` for async methods. Never use `async void` except for event handlers.
- **Dependency injection**: Register services in `Program.cs`. Use constructor injection.
- **LINQ**: Use method syntax for complex queries. Use query syntax for simple joins.
- **Nullable**: Enable nullable reference types. Handle nulls explicitly with `?.` and `??`.
{{/IF_DOTNET}}

{{#IF_ASPNET}}
## ASP.NET Core Conventions

- **Controllers**: Inherit from `ControllerBase` for APIs. Use `[ApiController]` attribute. Return `ActionResult<T>`.
- **Middleware**: Register in `Program.cs`. Order matters — auth before authorization.
- **Model validation**: Use data annotations or FluentValidation. Return `400` for validation errors.
- **Configuration**: Use `IOptions<T>` pattern. Never read config directly in services.
{{/IF_ASPNET}}

{{#IF_DART}}
## Dart Conventions

- **Naming**: Classes are `PascalCase`. Variables/functions are `camelCase`. Files are `snake_case.dart`.
- **Null safety**: Use `?` for nullable types. Use `!` only when certain. Prefer `??` for defaults.
- **Async**: Use `async`/`await`. Return `Future<T>`. Use `Stream<T>` for reactive data.
- **Effective Dart**: Follow official Effective Dart guidelines for style, documentation, and API design.
{{/IF_DART}}

{{#IF_FLUTTER}}
## Flutter Conventions

- **Widget structure**: Keep `build()` methods small. Extract sub-widgets as separate classes.
- **State management**: Use chosen state solution (Riverpod/Bloc/Provider) consistently. Never mix approaches.
- **Const constructors**: Use `const` wherever possible for widget constructors — improves rebuild performance.
- **Navigation**: Use declarative routing (go_router). Define routes in a central file.
- **Theming**: Use `ThemeData` for consistent styling. Access via `Theme.of(context)`.
{{/IF_FLUTTER}}

{{#IF_SWIFT}}
## Swift Conventions

- **Naming**: Types are `PascalCase`. Properties/methods are `camelCase`. Protocols describe capabilities (`Codable`, `Equatable`).
- **Optionals**: Prefer `guard let` and `if let` over force unwrapping. Use `??` for defaults.
- **Protocols**: Prefer protocol-oriented design. Define protocols for testability.
- **Value vs Reference**: Use structs for data. Use classes when identity matters or for reference semantics.
- **Access control**: Default to `private`. Expose only what's needed as `internal` or `public`.
{{/IF_SWIFT}}

{{#IF_SWIFTUI}}
## SwiftUI Conventions

- **View composition**: Break complex views into smaller sub-views. Use `ViewBuilder` for composable parts.
- **State**: `@State` for local state. `@Binding` for parent-owned state. `@ObservedObject`/`@StateObject` for external state.
- **Environment**: Use `@Environment` for system values. Use `@EnvironmentObject` for app-wide state.
- **Previews**: Provide previews with sample data for every view.
{{/IF_SWIFTUI}}

## Bug Fixing

Identify the EXACT file and component before patching. After fixing, grep the codebase for similar patterns that may need the same fix.

{{#IF_FRONTEND}}
## Design-to-Code Rules

When building from designs (Figma or .pen files):
- **Never neglect backgrounds** — apply every gradient, color, shadow
- **Always read UI library source** — check for default styles that override yours
- **Exact spacing** — match gap, padding, margin from the design exactly
- **Check every surface** — background, box-shadow, border, border-radius must all match
- **Use design agents** — figma-builder/pen-builder for building, figma-validator/pen-validator for verification
- **Visual compare** — always compare rendered output against the design
{{/IF_FRONTEND}}

